radialcolordialog

Class ColorRange

  • java.lang.Object
    • radialcolordialog.ColorRange

  • public class ColorRange
extends java.lang.Object
    This is a helper class for interpolating between two ColorTuples. This is used by the ColorBand to interpolate colors when painting/rendering.

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      ColorRange()
      Initialize a new ColorRange with default ColorTuples (where channel a = 1.0 to 0.0).

      • getTuple

        public ColorTuple getTuple(float t)
        Get the tuple of the 't' value. A 't' value of 0 will return the start tuple, where 1 will return the end tuple. Any other value will scale between the two.
        Parameters:
        t - The 't' value or scale of the range (0.0 to 1.0);
        Returns:
        The color tuple in the range based on 't';
